Files
=====
Fortran lexer: flexer.py
Fortran parser: fparser.py

The parser is configured in fparse.py, in the setup method. To regenerate the parser tables, 
simply parse a file and specify the --regen option at the end of the command line, e.g., in
the testfortran subdirectory:

    ../fparse.py t.f90 --regen

This will create the parsetab.py file and related tables in the correct directory (parsers).

To test the lexer, follow a similar approach, e.g., in testfortran: 
   ../flexer.py t.f90

